subSubSection.paragraph:
Male genitalia (Fig. 6
A-E
). Tegumen dorsally convex, subtriangular in lateral view, ventral projection wide; appendix angular reduced. Uncus straight, down curved at apex and dorsally keeled. Gnathos larger than uncus; straight and projected dorsally, without a ventral projection at base. Anterior projection of saccus cylindrical, length equal to tegumen. Valva subrectangular, with dorsal projections at apical third; costa developed and subtriangular; ventrally covered by setae. Aedeagus straight, thin and larger than valva; opening of aedeagus almost the total length of posterior portion.
